## Shell Application

This is the main shell application that coordinates all modules in the LEGO MOC Instructions platform. It provides:

- **Unified Authentication** - AWS Cognito integration with token management
- **Global Navigation** - Consistent header, sidebar, and routing
- **Module Coordination** - Lazy loading and error boundaries for feature modules
- **Theme Management** - Global theme provider with light/dark mode
- **Error Handling** - Global error boundaries and fallback UI

## Architecture

```
Shell App ({{kebabCase name}})
├── Authentication (AWS Cognito + Redux)
├── Routing (TanStack Router + Auth Guards)
├── Layout (Header, Sidebar, Footer)
├── Theme Provider (Global Tailwind)
└── Module Loading (Lazy loading + Error boundaries)
```

{{else if (eq type "module")}}
## Module Application

This is a feature module that plugs into the shell application ({{shellApp}}). It provides:

- **Feature-specific Components** - UI components for this module
- **Module State Management** - Local state with shared auth from shell
- **API Integration** - Uses shell's authentication for API calls
- **Lazy Loading** - Dynamically loaded by the shell application

## Integration

This module is registered in the shell app's routing configuration and loaded on-demand.

